CADI.Common.Session

Class ClientSideSessionTarget

  • java.lang.Object
    • CADI.Common.Session.SessionTarget
      • CADI.Common.Session.ClientSideSessionTarget
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ClientSessionTarget, ProxySessionTarget

    public class ClientSideSessionTarget
extends SessionTarget
    This class is used to save and manage data about a logical target belonging to a client session.

    Associated with each logical target are: - A single image data return type - A model of client's cache - One or more JPIP channels

    Usage example:
      constructor
      [setMethods]
      [newChannel]
      getMethdos

    Further information, please see see ISO/IEC 15444-1 section B.2

    Version:
    1.0.2 2011/03/07
    Author:
    Group on Interactive Coding of Images (GICI)

      • descriptorType

        protected int descriptorType
        Is the descriptor form type to be used in cache signaling.

        Allowed values are:
        DataBinsCacheManagement.NO_CACHE, DataBinsCacheManagement.EXPLICIT_FORM, DataBinsCacheManagement.IMPLICIT_FORM

      • descriptorQualifier

        protected int descriptorQualifier
        Is a qualifier of the descriptorType.

        Allowed values are:
        DataBinsCacheManagement.INDEX_RANGE, DataBinsCacheManagement.NUMBER_OF_BYTES, DataBinsCacheManagement.NUMBER_OF_LAYERS, DataBinsCacheManagement.WILDCARD.

      • fetchWindow

        public void fetchWindow(ViewWindowField requestViewWindow,
               boolean recordWOI)
                 throws ErrorException
        Fetch the compressed data belonging to the requestViewWindow from the server.

        Data are fetch but not decoded.

        Parameters:
        requestViewWindow - the target Window Of Interest to fetch.
        recordWOI -
        Throws:
        ErrorException - if an error occurs fetching the WOI.
        See Also:
        #getWindow(CADI.Common.Network.JPIP.ViewWindowField, boolean)}.

      • generateUID

        protected java.lang.String generateUID()
        Generates a unique identifier. The unique identifier generation is base on the current time, it is a time-stamp.

        NOTICE: this method must be improved adding the Rijndael (or another one), client information, etc. to improve the security.

        Returns:
        the unique channel identifier.

      • generateSID

        private java.lang.String generateSID()

        NOTICE: this method must be improved adding the Rijndael (or another one), client information, etc. to improve the security.

        Returns:
        the unique channel identifier.
